      "text": "A 60-year-old male patient presents to his family physician with complaints of fatigue, malaise, and unintentional weight loss for the past 6 months. On examination, the patient appears pale, and there is splenomegaly. The blood picture reveals anaemia, leukocytosis, and basophilia. Upon suspicion, genetic testing was done, and a diagnosis was made. Which of the following is the underlying genetic defect in this condition?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Translocation between chromosomes 12 and 21",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Unbalanced translocation between the long arm of chromosomes 9 and 22",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Deletion of chromosomes 11q, 13q, 17p",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Balanced translocation between the long arms of chromosomes 9 and 22",
          "correct": true
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "D. Balanced translocation between the long arms of chromosomes 9 and 22",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [
        "https://image.prepladder.com/notes/ubjfUdjgnTMSWByZT6yM1744697921.png",
        "https://image.prepladder.com/notes/Tu46dTeOSzd38UJYk3I81744698080.png"
      ],
      "explanation": "<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
      "bot": "@dams_new_robot",
      "audio": "",
      "video": "",
